# Legal Calculus — Tier 7 Starter (Modules 85–89)

**Purpose:** Procedural Memory & Public Archive. These modules help you build a parallel, verifiable record outside the courthouse.

| Module | Title | One‑line Summary | File |

|-------:|-------|------------------|------|

| 85 | Build the Archive — The Case File You Control | Stand up a public/private archive so truth survives clerk gates. | LC_Module_085_Build_the_Archive_The_Case_File_You_Control.docx |

| 86 | The Docket Mirror — Public Index & Timestamps | Publish a clean, hashed index so erasure becomes visible. | LC_Module_086_The_Docket_Mirror_Public_Index_and_Timestamps.docx |

| 87 | Chain of Custody for Evidence — Bates & Hash | Bates‑stamp + hash + declaration to make exhibits tamper‑evident. | LC_Module_087_Chain_of_Custody_for_Evidence_Bates_and_Hash.docx |

| 88 | Public Records & FOIA — Evidence the Court Forgot | Use FOIA/PRA to pull emails, logs, and metadata that fill gaps. | LC_Module_088_Public_Records_and_FOIA_Evidence_the_Court_Forgot.docx |

| 89 | Media Brief — Tell the Record Without Contempt | 200‑word factual brief with links to hashed PDFs. | LC_Module_089_Media_Brief_Tell_the_Record_Without_Contempt.docx |